<figureCitation id="136E2BF55559FFB551BBB856FC04FCE1" box="[907,958,847,874]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="50.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1486,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-369@50.[189,1398,1486,1852]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="Fig. 25. Closure of procoxal cavities of Platyope Fischer von Waldheim, 1820 and Earophanta Semenov, 1903, posterior view. A. Externally open procoxal cavities of Platyope unicolor Zubkov, 1829 (ZMSFU). B. Externally closed procoxal cavities of Earophanta serrata (Semenov, 1893), ♂ (ZIN). Arrows indicate postcoxal bridge. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419499/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">25B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136E2BF55559FFB551FBB856FBBAFCE2" box="[971,1024,847,873]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="52.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[290,1286,773,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-71@52.[281,1307,763,1783]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Fig. 26. Protibiae of Pimeliini, optic microscopy. A. Habrochiton vernus Semenov-Tjan-Shansky, 1907, ♂, lectotype (ZIN). B. Habrobates gabrieli (Schuster, 1935) comb. nov., paralectotype (NMB). C. Dietomorpha pardalis Kühnelt, 1957, ♂ (ZIN). D. Mantichorula semenowi Reitter, 1889, ♂ (ZIN). E. Przewalskia dilatata (Reitter, 1887), ♂ (ZIN). F. Apatopsis grombczewskii Semenov, 1891, ♀, paralectotype (ZIN). G. Earophanta serrata (Semenov, 1893), ♂ (ZIN). H. Platyope leucogramma (Pallas, 1773), ♂ (ZIN). Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419501" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419501/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">26G</figureCitation>
